0x0800 - IPv4 proto number in ethernet header
0x86dd - IPv6 proto number in ethernet header


3th and 4th bytes - ethernet protocol number
for ipv4(0x8000)
bytes 17-20 - src ip address
bytes 21-24 - dst ip address

ipv4:
10th byte - protocol number inside IP header (6 (0x6) - TCP, 17 (0x11) - UDP)

ipv4:
7th byte - protocol number inside IPv6 header (58 (0x3a) - ICMPv6)

validation upon reading from tun interface:
1. check proto number - 0x0800 - pass, 0x86dd - drop for now(no ipv6 support)
2. check src and dst addresses
